The course gives through lectures and seminars an overview of the formation of the Nordic language area as well as language situation today. The main focus is on the Scandinavian languages and their characteristic features.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives a historical survey of the formation of the Nordic language area as well as language situation today, provides basic knowledge of Scandinavian languages, their classification and characteristic features.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the course: - has an overview of the main features and the historical background of the formation of Nordic language area as well as language situation today; - knows the basic facts about the Scandinavian languages; - has an overview of the spreading of Scandinavian languages today; - is able to identify the Scandinavian language in which a text was written.
